  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 395&deg;F/ Gas 6</p>\r\n<p>Preheat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>bacon lardons</strong> and cook for 5 min or until starting to crisp&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once crisp, remove the pan from the heat and set aside&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/easy-bacon-and-asparagus-tarte-flambee/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the<strong> naan breads</strong> to a baking tray and put them in the oven for 5 min</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/easy-bacon-and-asparagus-tarte-flambee/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice the <strong>asparagus spears</strong> until you reach the tips &ndash; keep the tips whole</p>\r\n<p>Peel and chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel and slice the<strong> shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]&nbsp;</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/easy-bacon-and-asparagus-tarte-flambee/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>natural yoghurt</strong>, <strong>soft cheese</strong>, <strong>dried&nbsp;oregano</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>&nbsp;(Don't like raw garlic? Go easy!) and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> to a bowl&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Give everything a good old mix up &ndash; this is your <strong>creamy base&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/easy-bacon-and-asparagus-tarte-flambee/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped asparagus</strong> and <strong>shallot</strong> to the bacon pan and give everything a good mix up</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/easy-bacon-and-asparagus-tarte-flambee/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the baking tray from the oven and spread the<strong>&nbsp;creamy&nbsp;base</strong> over the <strong>naan breads</strong></p>\r\n<p>Top with the <strong>asparagus &amp; bacon mixture</strong>&nbsp;and put the tray in the oven for a further 10-12 min or until crispy &ndash; this is your&nbsp;<strong>bacon &amp; asparagus tarte flamb&eacute;e</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/easy-bacon-and-asparagus-tarte-flambee/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the<strong> Dijon mustard</strong> and <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong>&nbsp;with&nbsp;2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>in a small bowl &ndash; this is your <strong>balsamic dressing</strong></p>\r\n<p>Wash, then pat the <strong>lamb's lettuce</strong> dry</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/easy-bacon-and-asparagus-tarte-flambee/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dress the <strong>lamb's lettuce</strong> with the<strong> balsamic dressing</strong> and serve alongside the <strong>bacon &amp; asparagus tarte flamb&eacute;e</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
